  <original-body>ActiveSupport::Callbacks are used though out Rails so any micro-optimizations &quot;may&quot; go a long way.

At the moment, the callback's object is checked every time the callback is run, see Callback#evaluate_method. But we do know the type of this object when the callback object is created.

The idea is to have Callback#initialize generate a the &quot;Callback#call&quot; method (omg metaprogramming) that runs the conditionals :if/:unless then fires the callback.</original-body>
